<h2 id="never-mislead-with-data">2. Represent the data honestly</h2>
<p>Use honest scales, meaningful baselines and clear labels. Let the data speak for itself.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Use honest baselines and avoid truncating axes without clear indication.</li>
  <li>Keep time intervals and category order consistent.</li>
  <li>Label clearly so users can read values without guessing.</li>
</ul>

