<h4>Axis label orientation</h4>
<p>Keep all text horizontal where possible. Angled or vertical text is harder to read and fails more easily at 200% zoom and on mobile viewports.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Category labels:</strong> display horizontally. If labels are too long to fit horizontally, switch to a horizontal bar chart rather than rotating the text.</li>
  <li><strong>Axis titles:</strong> keep short enough to sit horizontally above (Y-axis) or beside (X-axis) the axis. Avoid vertical axis titles. Use the chart title and sub-title to carry that context.</li>
  <li><strong>Data labels:</strong> always horizontal.</li>
</ul>
<p>If rotating text cannot be avoided due to tool constraints, limit rotation to 45 degrees and ensure the text still meets the 12px minimum size at all viewport widths.</p>

